Author: Alt-Options

This library provides some methods that should make it easy to communicate with the Yahoo Finance API. 
It allows you to request detailed information, some statistics and historical quotes on stocks. Separate functionality is available to request a simple FX quote.

Step 1:
Figure out what kind of data do you need from the explorer.
A good website to start is the following:
https://developer.yahoo.com/yql/console/
http://financequotes-api.com/

Step 2:
Figure out how to pull the date that you need with the right syntax.

Step 3:
Implement it in your code.
